This repository contains puppet module for installing Sun jdk6 on Ubuntu. This module enables unattended installation of Sun Java package agreeing to license agreement.

How to use it:

1. Import this project in your puppet master machine module.

	include sun-jdk6

2. Adjust fileserver.conf configuration as per your requirement 

				  OR

   Replace the existing fileserver.conf file with given file.

3. Copy given "etc" folder structure on your puppet file server as
   per your above custom fileserver.conf configuration 
	
                          OR

   Copy the whole "etc" folder under your /opt folder on file server
   if you are using give fileserver.conf file.


